  <bioghist id="aspace_377f2e6b3a2fc884e224dc9d0057026a">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The Cornell University Senate was formed in 1970. Its predecessor, the Constituent Assembly, provided the preliminary organization. In 1977 the CU Senate was replaced by the Cornell Faculty Council of Representatives and in February 1996 this was replaced by the Faculty Senate.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_c184ba526110147784f3128a40b06a2a">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Includes correspondence, minutes, reports, rosters, and legislation of the Senate; correspondence of the speaker of the Senate; correspondence, minutes, reports, and legislation of the Campus Life Committee, the Executive Committee, and other Senate committees; file concerning the establishment of the Senate; tape recordings of sessions of the Senate and of the Executive Committee; and records of the Senate's predecessor organization, the Constituent Assembly.</p>  </scopecontent>
